\contentsline {added}{Added: \truncate {\Changestruncatewidth }{The main experiments used in this chapter are the pre-industrial control (piControl), AMIP, and historical experiments. The pre-industrial control experiments use a constant external forcing for the year 1850, and are relatively longer integrations \citep {menary2018}, whereas the historical experiments use our best estimate of the time-varying aerosol and greenhouse gas emissions from 1850 to 2014 \citep {eyring2016,andrews2020}. The AMIP experiments use the same external forcing as the historical experiments but also "nudge" the SSTs using observational products, thereby decoupling the atmosphere from the ocean and removing SST biases \citep {eyring2016}.}}{118}{section*.104}%
